 in: violin, viola, violoncello, double bass, harp, guitar, flute, oboe, clarinet, bassoon, saxophone, trumpet, French horn, trombone, euphonium, tuba, percussion, and multiple woodwinds. Current and former students have won prizes in major instrumental competitions of every genre, and are appointed to professional positions in orchestras, wind symphonies, and universities/conservatories spanning the world. Degrees Bachelor of Music Master of Music Doctor of Musical Arts Each with major in performance and specialization: bassoon, clarinet, double bass, euphonium, flute, French horn, guitar, harp, oboe, percussion, saxophone, trombone (bass and tenor), trumpet, viola, violin, violoncello, voice Area Websites Clarinet Euphonium Harp Oboe Percussion Saxophone Strings Trombone Trumpet Tuba Faculty Gideon F. Alorwoyie - Percussion Jose Aponte - Percussion Tony Baker - Trombone Jason Bergman - Trumpet Brian Bowman - Coordinator of Brass; Euphonium Jeff Bradetich - Double Bass Julia Bushkova - Violin Kris Chesky - Texas Center for Music & Medicine Mary Karen Clardy - Flute Fabiana Claure - Music Entrepreneurship Daryl Coad - Clarinet Christopher Deane - Percussion Susan Dubois - Coordinator of Strings; Viola Deborah Fabian - Clarinet Mark Ford - Coordinator of Percussion Daphne Gerling - Viola Adam Gordon - Baroque Trumpet Jaymee Haefner - Director of Undergraduate Studies/Harp John Holt - Chair of Instrumental Studies; Trumpet Thomas Johnson - Guitar Philip Lewis - Violin Donald Little - Tuba Kimberly Cole Luevano - Clarinet Natalie Mannix - Trombone Steven Menard - Trombone Eric Nestler - Saxophone Felix Olschofka - Violin Eugene Osadchy - Cello Gudrun Raschen - Double Bass Paul Rennick - Percussion Kathleen Reynolds - Coordinator of Woodwinds; Bassoon Cynthia Roberts - Baroque Violin Nikola Ruzevic - Cello and Coordinator of Chamber Music James Ryon - Oboe William Scharnberg - Horn James Scott - Flute John Scott - Clarinet Terri Sundberg - Flute Adam Whear - Baroque Cel